      <div id="main">
            <h1>About</h1>

            

            <p>The Gotham Ruby Conference (GoRuCo) is a one-day event that will take place in New York City on Saturday, April 26th. It will be a technical conference aimed at highly motivated programmers interested in all things Ruby. You&#8217;ll spend the day among Rubyists, Rails developers, and language enthusiasts in New York City, home of Silicon Alley. The <a href="/agenda/">agenda</a> will feature <a href="/speakers/">five speakers</a> and an open session of lightning talks by attendees.</p>


	<p>We&#8217;ll be starting the day at 9:00 am with registration, and the last talk will conclude at 6:45 pm. Pace University will be providing the venue. We can accommodate a wide range of dietary restrictions; if you have any special needs you should contact us at <a href="mailto:info@goruco.com">info@goruco.com</a>. An afterparty for attendees will be provided at a local bar later that evening.</p>


	<p>Attendance is limited to 120 people.</p>


	<p>To keep up with conference news, subscribe to our <a href="/rss/"><span class="caps">RSS</span> feed</a>. If you have any questions, please contact us at <a href="mailto:info@goruco.com">info@goruco.com</a>.</p>


	<p>GoRuCo is organized by <a href="/organizers/">volunteers</a> from <a href="http://nycruby.org/"><span class="caps">NYC</span>.rb</a> and other New York-area rubyists.</p>
            
            
